text_blocks.snippet: Yes, AirPods 4 are generally considered worth it, especially the ANC (Active Noise Cancellation) model, offering significant upgrades in sound quality, comfort, and features like Adaptive Audio and Spatial Audio for a better overall experience, though they still sit below the premium AirPods Pro series, particularly in noise isolation and battery with ANC. For those coming from older models (1st/2nd Gen), the jump is substantial, while the choice between AirPods 4 ANC and AirPods Pro 3 depends on budget and preference for sealed-fit comfort versus open-fit convenience.
snippet_highlighted_words: Yes, AirPods 4 are generally considered worth it

text_blocks.snippet: This video provides a detailed comparison to help you decide if AirPods 4 are the right choice for you:
Key Reasons They're Worth It (Especially ANC Model)

list.title: Improved Sound:
list.snippet: Enhanced bass and clearer sound compared to older standard models, rivaling Pro models in some areas.

list.title: Effective ANC:
list.snippet: The noise cancellation in the ANC version is surprisingly good for an open-fit earbud, making commutes better.

list.title: Adaptive Audio:
list.snippet: Blends Transparency and ANC for seamless environmental awareness.

list.title: Comfort & Fit:
list.snippet: Redesigned for a more secure and natural fit for more users, with updated stems and force sensors.

list.title: Value:
list.snippet: The ANC model offers Pro-like features at a lower price point than Pro earbuds, making them a great value upgrade.

list.title: Open Fit vs. Sealed:
list.snippet: The open design means less passive noise isolation than the silicone-tipped AirPods Pro, which can affect deep bass and quiet environments.

list.title: Battery Life (with ANC):
list.snippet: Can be shorter when ANC is active, requiring more frequent charging compared to AirPods Pro with their larger case.

list.title: No On-Ear Volume Control:
list.snippet: Volume control is still managed via the connected device or Siri, unlike the stem controls on AirPods Pro.

text_blocks.snippet: This video explains why the AirPods 4 ANC model may still be a good buy even a year after its release:

list.snippet: Upgrade from 1st/2nd Gen: A definite "yes" for a significant upgrade in sound, features, and comfort.
Value Seekers: The ANC model offers a compelling package close to Pro features at a better price.
Comfort-Focused Users: If sealed tips bother you, the comfortable open fit is a major plus.
Ultimate Noise Cancellation: If blocking out the world is your top priority.
Longer Battery with ANC: If you need all-day ANC performance.
Volume Control on Earbuds: For quick volume adjustments without reaching for your phone.
